      </table-wrap>
      <p>In addition, the distribution of the three estimators across samples showed that RE and CVE had little variability between cases, as expected since a similar set of samples was used in all cases (Figure <xref rid="F4" ref-type="fig">4</xref>). Further analysis of the data looking at each fold shows a lack of variation between folds too, except for a few outliers in ANN (Figure <xref rid="F5" ref-type="fig">5</xref>). In contrast, SOE varied within a broader range: for all the algorithms, a difference &gt;0.2 was observed from the sample with the lowest AUC to the one with the largest AUC.</p>
